<p>My name is Vanilla Chi, a New York-based illustrator, amateur graphic designer and animator, part-time art bookmaker. Iâ€™m currently a senior in the BFA illustration department at the School of Visual Arts.&nbsp;</p>



<p>My inspiration comes from my strong nostalgia and personal pain. Because of Covid-19, I have not been back to China for almost two years. I miss my family and hometown. In Chinese traditional culture, we trust everyone has a &#8220;root&#8221;. For me, the root is like an elastic rope &#8211; the longer I am away from home, the more elastic the rope becomes. Now, I almost cannot take the weight of the elasticity, and my work has become a reflection.</p>



