<p>Besides, nostalgia can selectively filter memories to beautify or even strengthen the content of yesteryear&#8217;s life; it can also expose scars to affirm the present-day me. My artistic expression is actually based on my very personal memories: I always drew girls and dresses when I grew up, because I couldn&#8217;t get the dress I liked as a child; I drew bullying and loneliness, because I was hated and disliked by my classmates; I drew carnival and stage show with excessive abundance and bright colors, because I was nostalgic for toys, amusement parks, and carnivals.</p>



<p>I drew expressionless, uniform little boys and girls, because of the pain and depression I feel, but cannot show in concern of annoying people. These experiences constitute who I am I work with my memories in order to produce an honest expression.</p>



